# Prep Your Mindset

## Read Upgrade Your Technical Skills with Deliberate Practice. (10 minutes)

- focused and intentional practice methods that contribute to skill improvement.

## Watch Carol Dweck on the Growth Mindset. (10 minutes)

- our abilities and intelligence can grow through hard work and dedication. It's all about embracing challenges with a positive attitude toward learning.

## Watch Angela Lee Duckworth on Grit. (6 minutes)

- Angela Lee Duckworth talk about grit, which is about sticking with your goals despite setbacks. This short video may inspire you to develop resilience and determination for long-term success.

## Watch Alain de Botton on Redefining Success. (17 minutes)

- Botton's talk on redefining success. This video might challenge traditional ideas about success and encourage you to think about what success means to you personally.

## Assess your emotional intelligence. If you have done it in the past, now you can identify the areas you have grown in recently.

- Reflect on your emotional intelligence, considering aspects like self-awareness, self-regulation, empathy, and social skills. This self-assessment can help you identify areas where you excel and areas where there's room for growth.

## Assess your biases. If you have done it in the past, now you can identify the areas you have grown in recently.

- Reflect on your biases and consider how they might influence your decisions. This assessment is about recognizing and addressing any implicit biases you may have. Identifying areas of growth in this area shows progress in promoting fair and unbiased perspectives.